---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | SexualHarassmentCalc';
const description = 'Privacy policy for SexualHarassmentCalc: what we collect, third-party advertising, cookies, and your rights.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><em>Updated May 18, 2026.</em></p>

  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how SexualHarassmentCalc (&ldquo;the Site,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us&rdquo;) collects,
    uses, and shares information about visitors. The Site is operated by The Click Lab and is informational only.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>
    The Site does not require accounts and does not ask for personal information to view content or use the calculator. We collect
    the following automatically:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Server logs.</strong> Standard request logs including IP address, user-agent string, referring URL, and timestamp. Used for security, abuse prevention, and aggregate traffic analysis.</li>
    <li><strong>Calculator inputs.</strong> Values you enter into the calculator are processed in your browser only and are not transmitted to or stored on our servers.</li>
    <li><strong>Email correspondence.</strong> If you email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>, we retain the message and your email address to respond. We do not share or republish reader correspondence.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Third-party advertising</h2>
  <p>
    The Site displays advertising through <strong>Google AdSense</strong> (publisher ID pub-6434377544325972). Google and its
    advertising partners may use cookies, web beacons, and similar technologies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this
    site and other sites. Google&rsquo;s use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your visit
    to our site and other sites on the internet. You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting
    <a href="https://adssettings.google.com">Google Ads Settings</a> or
    <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices">www.aboutads.info/choices</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    The Site itself does not set first-party tracking cookies. Third-party advertising scripts loaded by Google AdSense may set
    cookies as described above. You can disable cookies entirely in your browser settings; some site features may not work, but
    the calculator and all content will remain available.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    The Site is not directed to children under 13 and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you
    believe a child has provided personal information through the Site, contact us and we will delete it.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to request access to, correction of, or deletion of personal information
    we hold about you, and to opt out of certain processing. California residents have rights under the CCPA/CPRA; EU/UK residents
    have rights under GDPR/UK GDPR. To exercise these rights, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>
    with the page URL and the nature of your request. We respond within 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    Server logs are retained for up to 90 days. Email correspondence is retained as long as needed to respond and for a reasonable
    period afterward for audit and abuse prevention.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    The Site is served over HTTPS. We do not store personal information beyond email correspondence and standard server logs.
    No internet transmission is fully secure; do not include information in email to us that you would not be comfortable putting
    in a non-confidential medium.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy as the Site evolves or as law requires. Material changes will be reflected in the &ldquo;Updated&rdquo;
    date at the top of this page. Continued use of the Site after a change constitutes acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
